    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Phila<lb/>
            May 23rd<lb/>
            1873.<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Mr Morais&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>I feel so very sorry that<lb/> I <sic>cant</sic> hear Henry read his<lb/> Portion tomorrow&#44; that I must<lb/> write &#38; tell you so.  I am<lb/> sure you will be very happy<lb/> on the occasion&#44; and I hope<lb/> his sainted mother may<lb/> look down&#44; and bless him&#44;<lb/> that he may grow in wisdom&#44;<lb/> in prosperity&#44; and in good<lb/>ness&#8212;and that he may be<lb/> worthy of the great good&#44;<lb/> which is in store for those<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>who fear Him and keep<lb/> his Holy name&#44; and his<lb/> commandments.  I wish<lb/> I had some Rich &#38; Rave<lb/> offering&#44; for your son&#44; on<lb/> this eventful day&#44; but<lb/> Bibles &#38; Prayer books he has<lb/> plenty&#8212;and Jewels I have<lb/> none&#8212;but hearty good<lb/> wishes&#44; from yours &#38; his<lb/></p>
            <p>sincere friend<lb/>
            Sara Mordecai<lb/></p>

        </body>
    </text>
